==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɪˈklɛktɪk/}}, {{SAMPA|/I"klEktIk/}}

===Etymology===
from {{etyl|fr}} [[éclectique]], from {{etyl|el}} eklektikos "selective," literally "picking out", from eklektos, past participle of eklegein "pick out, select", itself from ek "out" + legein "gather, choose". Originally an Ancient group of  philosophers who selected their favorite doctrines from every system. Compare with {{etyl|la}} ''[[electionem]]'' ([[election]]).

